  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Horn Food Price Crisis Response for Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Focusing on the most vulnerable within targeted areas, activities under the Seed Systems and Agricultural Inputs sub-sector have been designed to provide near-term stabilization of humanitarian indicators in food insecure households through the provision of cash and productive assets (seeds, equipment, etc). HFPCR improve animal health services by strengthening the capacity of private Community-based Animal Health Workers and government animal health service providers. As cattle and small ruminants constitute such an important component of pastoral livelihoods, they are the primary focus of vaccinations undertaken by the HFPCR project. In promotion of long-term development objectives, including the diversification of asset bases and development of market linkages, a participatory approach to community economic development is engaged. Sector 2 activities utilize a Local Economic Development framework to articulate a medium-to-long term vision for cluster-based economic development, prioritizing sub-sectors, and laying-out concrete means by which selected value chains are enhanced.</narrative>
  </description>
